in the basement of our house,
where we used to cook.

828
01:03:28,555 --> 01:03:30,887
It was for our business.

829
01:03:35,270 --> 01:03:36,726
Are you thirsty?

830
01:03:36,813 --> 01:03:39,100
Phoenix is slowly connecting the dots.

831
01:03:46,448 --> 01:03:47,779
[chuckles]

832
01:03:51,286 --> 01:03:52,617
[Josephine] Tara?

833
01:03:54,414 --> 01:03:55,825
I'm dying.

834
01:03:55,915 --> 01:03:56,905
What?

835
01:03:58,585 --> 01:04:01,122
The smoke from the chemicals...

836
01:04:01,838 --> 01:04:05,581
poisoned my blood
and badly damaged my heart.

837
01:04:05,675 --> 01:04:08,713
I don't think I have much time left.

838
01:04:08,803 --> 01:04:10,464
Is there anything you can do?

839
01:04:10,555 --> 01:04:12,592
[Josephine giggles]

840
01:04:20,106 --> 01:04:23,690
I heard you left flowers for me
at our old house.

841
01:04:27,697 --> 01:04:32,157
I love it how, the approach, and going
back to the idea of the fairy tale.

842
01:04:32,243 --> 01:04:34,735
Right now, we realize that
these knights that saved her

843
01:04:34,829 --> 01:04:37,867
were actually working for the evil witch

844
01:04:37,957 --> 01:04:42,167
and the evil witch, what she wants,
just like in Snow White,

845
01:04:42,253 --> 01:04:48,920
she wants to absorb the youth
out of Phoenix for herself.

846
01:04:51,137 --> 01:04:54,050
It's very, of course, twisted.

847
01:04:55,642 --> 01:04:57,132
I need a new heart, baby.

848
01:04:57,227 --> 01:05:00,390
A very twisted concept,
she being her mother.

849
01:05:00,480 --> 01:05:04,644
Her thought process is, you know,
"I gave you life once,

850
01:05:04,734 --> 01:05:06,475
and now I need it back.

851
01:05:07,153 --> 01:05:09,770
And you should give it to me
gracefully and willingly."

852
01:05:13,827 --> 01:05:15,693
Like a direct relative.

853
01:05:15,787 --> 01:05:17,448
Which is what she's trying to do.

854
01:05:17,539 --> 01:05:22,284
Because she just might as well
just move ahead with the surgery,

855
01:05:22,377 --> 01:05:23,412
and that's it.

856
01:05:23,503 --> 01:05:25,744
But she wants to convince her

857
01:05:26,631 --> 01:05:32,092
to give out her heart willingly
out of love for her.

858
01:05:32,178 --> 01:05:33,668
That's what she wants.

859
01:05:35,432 --> 01:05:41,348
So that she can sleep at night
without any sort of remorse.

860
01:05:47,986 --> 01:05:51,900
And this shot, I think,
is very much of a fairy tale,

861
01:05:53,700 --> 01:05:57,193
the hand hovering on top of her
as she passes out.

862
01:06:00,790 --> 01:06:06,911
Going back to the Blind Man, a light
of hope on the horizon as he wakes up.

863
01:06:07,005 --> 01:06:09,246
[grunting]

864
01:06:17,307 --> 01:06:19,344
[groaning]

865
01:06:20,477 --> 01:06:22,218
[dog panting]

866
01:06:26,524 --> 01:06:27,514
[Norman] Go home.

867
01:06:27,609 --> 01:06:28,974
[metal clinking]

868
01:06:29,068 --> 01:06:31,400
-[dog whines]
-Shh.

869
01:06:31,488 --> 01:06:33,229
-[whines]
-Shh!

870
01:06:37,577 --> 01:06:39,363
[metal clinking]

871
01:06:51,299 --> 01:06:56,089
I love how the sound design
plays into the story here

872
01:06:56,179 --> 01:07:02,846
and how we get into the Blind Man's head
and experience how he perceives the world

873
01:07:02,936 --> 01:07:06,304
through his hearing.

874
01:07:07,148 --> 01:07:13,565
And that guides him to discover
Hernandez's van and her body.

875
01:07:26,251 --> 01:07:27,958
[clinking]

876
01:08:01,119 --> 01:08:02,484
[sobs]

877
01:08:06,332 --> 01:08:11,452
At this point, we feel that the Blind Man
is starting to slowly understand

878
01:08:12,130 --> 01:08:17,341
all the pain that he has caused,
all the death,

879
01:08:18,219 --> 01:08:22,554
the trail of death that he's left behind
because of his actions.

880
01:08:23,224 --> 01:08:26,091
Because Hernandez would be alive
if it wasn't for him.

881
01:08:28,187 --> 01:08:29,803
[dog panting]

882
01:08:33,443 --> 01:08:34,478
Stay.

883
01:08:36,988 --> 01:08:42,028
I love this idea on how he finds a way
to track down these guys...

884
01:08:45,079 --> 01:08:49,698
and get to Phoenix using the dog.

885
01:08:50,668 --> 01:08:54,286
He knows dogs and he knows that the dog
is going to go back home,

886
01:08:54,380 --> 01:08:55,620
wherever that home is.

887
01:08:55,715 --> 01:09:00,175
So he just has to follow the dog
and that's it.

888
01:09:01,095 --> 01:09:03,211
I think that idea, at a script level,

889
01:09:03,306 --> 01:09:05,923
it took us months
to come up with that idea

890
01:09:06,017 --> 01:09:10,682
and figure out how the hell the Blind Man
was going to find these guys.

891
01:09:10,772 --> 01:09:11,762
Go home.

892
01:09:11,856 --> 01:09:13,472
But at the end, I think it works great.

893
01:09:13,566 --> 01:09:16,274
I think was Fede's idea,
and I think it's genius.

894
01:09:21,115 --> 01:09:22,321
Go home.

895
01:09:24,118 --> 01:09:25,529
[dripping]

896
01:09:32,877 --> 01:09:36,541
I think this is the last shot
that we shot in the movie.

897
01:09:37,548 --> 01:09:38,879
[chuckles]

898
01:09:44,806 --> 01:09:46,717
[drill whirring]

899
01:10:03,741 --> 01:10:06,984
I hope you understand
the high risks of this procedure.

900
01:10:08,621 --> 01:10:12,159
[Raylan] I think I pay you enough.
Shut up and do your job.

901
01:10:13,668 --> 01:10:15,454
Why is she still alive?

902
01:10:16,921 --> 01:10:19,253
[surgeon] If she's dead, so is her heart.

903
01:10:20,675 --> 01:10:24,418
And I can't keep it fresh long enough
without the proper equipment.

904
01:10:26,597 --> 01:10:28,964
[laughing] That is so creepy.

905
01:10:30,768 --> 01:10:35,262
And I like this beat,
you know, Mother just calls her

906
01:10:35,940 --> 01:10:39,058
and says, "Thank you."

907
01:10:39,152 --> 01:10:40,392
I think that is so creepy.

908
01:10:40,486 --> 01:10:45,731
And that is tied to that idea
that the mother convinced herself

909
01:10:45,825 --> 01:10:51,161
that Phoenix was doing this willingly,
you know, and she just thanks her.

910
01:11:01,424 --> 01:11:02,755
What's wrong with you, man?

911
01:11:05,011 --> 01:11:10,506
Come back to Raul, and we show how
he is growing a conscience

912
01:11:10,600 --> 01:11:13,843
and he's slowly switching sides.

913
01:11:13,936 --> 01:11:15,301
You know, he's not--

914
01:11:15,396 --> 01:11:19,264
He probably didn't know exactly what
these guys were going to do to that girl.

915
01:11:19,358 --> 01:11:24,068
And now he just feels like
he can't go with it.

916
01:11:24,155 --> 01:11:25,566
It's just too much.

917
01:11:26,282 --> 01:11:30,651
I love it when you give these villains,
these henchmen,

918
01:11:30,745 --> 01:11:34,830
when you give them some depth,
and you get to understand

919
01:11:34,916 --> 01:11:38,580
what their moral compass is
and, you know, what their code is.

920
01:11:38,669 --> 01:11:41,661
There's things that they would do,
but some things they wouldn't.

921
01:11:41,756 --> 01:11:45,670
Of course, Jim-Bob, the other guy,
is a total psychopath. He's cool with it.

922
01:11:45,760 --> 01:11:49,298
He just cares about their business
and the money

923
01:11:49,388 --> 01:11:51,470
and they need her and that's it.

924
01:11:51,557 --> 01:11:52,968
[drill whirring]

925
01:12:02,151 --> 01:12:03,141
Boom.

926
01:12:05,530 --> 01:12:06,861
What the fuck?

927
01:12:06,948 --> 01:12:08,609
[crash]

928
01:12:12,328 --> 01:12:13,318
Go check it out.

929
01:12:23,297 --> 01:12:25,083
[door opens, closes]

930
01:12:51,325 --> 01:12:52,815
[rats squeaking]

931
01:12:52,910 --> 01:12:54,901
Rats. Real rats.

932
01:13:02,086 --> 01:13:04,123
I love this next shot.

933
01:13:04,213 --> 01:13:07,422
It will reveal the Blind Man.

934
01:13:08,926 --> 01:13:10,337
I think it's beautiful.

935
01:13:12,763 --> 01:13:14,879
-[grunting]
-[gunshots]

936
01:13:26,360 --> 01:13:30,319
Of course, the sound of the water
pouring down makes it very difficult

937
01:13:30,406 --> 01:13:36,152
for the Blind Man to locate Jim-Bob.

938
01:13:36,245 --> 01:13:38,156
He's confused.

939
01:13:38,247 --> 01:13:39,908
His radar is off.

940
01:13:40,541 --> 01:13:42,578
And he just takes a beating.

941
01:13:49,175 --> 01:13:54,511
But he's got his tricks, of course.

942
01:13:56,098 --> 01:13:57,304
[groaning]

943
01:13:59,852 --> 01:14:03,470
I'm gonna carve your fucking head open
like a pumpkin, man.

944
01:14:03,564 --> 01:14:05,100
[grunting]

945
01:14:05,191 --> 01:14:06,773
-[bones crack]
-[screaming]

946
01:14:06,859 --> 01:14:07,894
[choking]

947
01:14:16,869 --> 01:14:18,701
[choking]

948
01:14:20,164 --> 01:14:21,370
I love this idea.

949
01:14:21,457 --> 01:14:25,041
Jim-Bob needs to make a run for the gun,
but he's going to make a sound as well.

950
01:14:26,629 --> 01:14:28,916
But he takes a risk. Boom.

951
01:14:39,266 --> 01:14:40,677
[choking]

952
01:14:48,985 --> 01:14:50,271
[grunting]

953
01:14:59,412 --> 01:15:01,323
This is for Shadow.

954
01:15:03,040 --> 01:15:04,075
Oh, fuck.

955
01:15:04,792 --> 01:15:06,078
No!

956
01:15:06,168 --> 01:15:08,660
That hammer went down really hard.

957
01:15:08,754 --> 01:15:11,792
And it was a heavy hammer,
because it's a one-piece iron hammer.

958
01:15:11,882 --> 01:15:16,592
And Stephen Lang, you know,
just went at it.

959
01:15:16,679 --> 01:15:19,842
And Adam was actually there

960
01:15:19,932 --> 01:15:24,472
when Slang was hitting the ground.

961
01:15:24,562 --> 01:15:29,898
So he had to move in order
to avoid getting hit by the hammer.

962
01:15:30,609 --> 01:15:35,604
So it was very stressful for Adam
to shoot that scene.

963
01:15:40,536 --> 01:15:42,994
Disloyal fucking animal.

964
01:15:43,080 --> 01:15:48,075
I love it how the dog
also has an arc in this movie.

965
01:15:48,169 --> 01:15:51,912
-Everything's okay, I promise.
-Baby, should I be worried?

966
01:15:52,006 --> 01:15:53,417
No, no. Not at all.

967
01:15:53,507 --> 01:15:54,918
I got you. I got you.

968
01:15:55,009 --> 01:15:56,750
I can't work without power.

969
01:15:59,722 --> 01:16:01,258
Change of plans, then.

970
01:16:02,308 --> 01:16:04,219
Pack your things. Bring the girl.

971
01:16:04,310 --> 01:16:05,471
Raul.

972
01:16:07,271 --> 01:16:09,638
-Bring the men. Kill the blind man.
-How many of us?

973
01:16:09,732 --> 01:16:11,894
All of you!

974
01:16:15,404 --> 01:16:16,565
Let's go.

975
01:16:20,701 --> 01:16:22,942
I love the scene that's coming up next.

976
01:16:27,875 --> 01:16:30,583
On paper, you know, we made total sense.

977
01:16:30,669 --> 01:16:32,455
We thought of the idea with Fede

978
01:16:32,546 --> 01:16:36,631
that these guys are going to walk
into that pool,

979
01:16:36,717 --> 01:16:41,678
and the water ripples are going
to make contact with the Blind Man's hand

980
01:16:41,764 --> 01:16:44,722
and then he knows where these guys are,
and he shoots.

981
01:16:44,809 --> 01:16:49,929
But then, you know, shooting that on set
was a different story.

982
01:16:50,022 --> 01:16:53,481
You know, being able to capture
those water ripples,

983
01:16:53,567 --> 01:16:58,107
it was a huge challenge
in terms of lighting and camera movement.

984
01:16:58,197 --> 01:17:00,734
It wasn't easy,
but we got very, very lucky.

985
01:17:00,825 --> 01:17:05,114
And our team were such professionals
and so good at what they do.

986
01:17:05,204 --> 01:17:10,870
They were actually able
to pull it off pretty quickly, I think.

987
01:17:13,170 --> 01:17:18,006
I think this next shot, this is the camera
following that actual water ripple.

988
01:17:18,926 --> 01:17:20,382
It was just perfect.

989
01:17:31,188 --> 01:17:32,178
[spluttering]

990
01:17:38,821 --> 01:17:44,567
In this moment, I love it, because
the Blind Man is totally defenseless now.

991
01:17:44,660 --> 01:17:47,027
He's at the mercy of this guy.

992
01:17:49,623 --> 01:17:50,784
<i>They're gonna kill her.</i>

993
01:17:56,046 --> 01:17:57,707
And that's not cool with me.

994
01:17:58,799 --> 01:18:00,665
But now he switched sides.

995
01:18:00,759 --> 01:18:04,047
He's grown in consciousness.

996
01:18:04,138 --> 01:18:07,472
And because of that,
you know, he saves the day.

997
01:18:07,558 --> 01:18:09,299
He actually saves the girl.

998
01:18:15,816 --> 01:18:17,227
But he's relieved.

999
01:18:21,238 --> 01:18:22,228
Go left.

1000
01:18:24,074 --> 01:18:25,064
That way.

1001
01:18:28,579 --> 01:18:30,161
He'll kill you all.

1002
01:18:40,591 --> 01:18:44,550
Now we enter the biggest scene
in the whole movie.

1003
01:18:45,971 --> 01:18:49,805
This, I think, took, like,
seven or eight days to shoot--

1004
01:18:51,644 --> 01:18:55,137
To shoot the scene,
plus a couple days of second unit.

1005
01:18:56,649 --> 01:18:59,311
And this place is actually--
This is Belgrade.

1006
01:18:59,401 --> 01:19:04,692
And this swimming pool is in--

1007
01:19:04,782 --> 01:19:08,650
Marshal Tito,
who was the leader of Yugoslavia,

1008
01:19:08,744 --> 01:19:10,530
it's his palace.

1009
01:19:14,833 --> 01:19:15,823
[Josephine] Baby.

1010
01:19:15,918 --> 01:19:17,625
Shh. It's okay.

1011
01:19:17,711 --> 01:19:19,076
-Stop it.
-[grunts]

1012
01:19:20,339 --> 01:19:25,084
The swimming pool is not that deep,
but we enhanced it in CG

1013
01:19:25,177 --> 01:19:27,839
and we made it to be a diving pool,

1014
01:19:29,014 --> 01:19:31,631
which are usually 20 feet deep
or something.

1015
01:19:31,725 --> 01:19:35,719
Deep enough to where if you fall into it,
you've probably killed yourself.

1016
01:19:52,788 --> 01:19:55,325
I love this red smoke scene.

1017
01:19:56,083 --> 01:19:57,164
Very intense.

1018
01:19:57,251 --> 01:19:58,286
[Raylan] I can't see you.

1019
01:20:07,469 --> 01:20:08,880
-Baby?
-[clattering]

1020
01:20:14,643 --> 01:20:16,429
[grunting]

1021
01:20:17,146 --> 01:20:18,557
[footsteps running]

1022
01:20:19,189 --> 01:20:20,520
[man grunting]

1023
01:20:22,943 --> 01:20:24,684
[grunting]

1024
01:20:25,904 --> 01:20:28,191
[coughing]

1025
01:20:28,282 --> 01:20:30,148
[panting]

1026
01:20:41,462 --> 01:20:43,373
[Josephine] Someone's here! Hurry!

1027
01:20:44,757 --> 01:20:45,997
Baby?

1028
01:20:51,013 --> 01:20:52,629
[grunting]

1029
01:20:52,723 --> 01:20:53,758
[coughing]

1030
01:20:56,643 --> 01:20:58,805
[gun clicking]

1031
01:20:58,896 --> 01:21:02,059
I love this moment.
This is connected to the first movie where

1032
01:21:02,149 --> 01:21:05,858
the Blind Man accidentally shoots Cindy,

1033
01:21:05,944 --> 01:21:09,153
the girl that he trapped in the basement.

1034
01:21:10,074 --> 01:21:14,193
He thinks he shot one of the intruders,
but he ended up killing her.

1035
01:21:14,286 --> 01:21:15,697
And this is the same thing.

1036
01:21:15,788 --> 01:21:21,158
Raylan thinks that he got the Blind Man,
but he just killed his wife.

1037
01:21:23,170 --> 01:21:24,251
No.

1038
01:21:24,338 --> 01:21:25,954
No!

1039
01:21:26,048 --> 01:21:27,755
No!

1040
01:21:28,300 --> 01:21:29,882
[grunting]

1041
01:21:39,686 --> 01:21:40,676
[Phoenix] No!

1042
01:21:44,691 --> 01:21:46,022
[wheels skidding]

1043
01:21:46,110 --> 01:21:47,646
[screaming]

1044
01:21:52,616 --> 01:21:53,822
I love this.

1045
01:21:53,909 --> 01:21:56,947
This is one of those "good news, bad news"
action set pieces, you know.

1046
01:21:57,037 --> 01:21:58,903
Good news, Mother is dead.

1047
01:21:58,997 --> 01:22:03,662
Bad news, she's now going to drag
Phoenix into the swimming pool.

1048
01:22:04,461 --> 01:22:06,748
Good news, there's a machete.

1049
01:22:11,218 --> 01:22:15,928
Bad news, I cannot chop the arm in time,

1050
01:22:17,057 --> 01:22:19,799
and I'm dragged into the swimming pool.

1051
01:22:19,893 --> 01:22:23,261
And also the Blind Man
appears to be losing his fight.

1052
01:22:23,355 --> 01:22:25,096
-[grunting]
-[screaming]

1053
01:22:25,190 --> 01:22:26,271
[bones crack]

1054
01:22:32,906 --> 01:22:34,112
Phoenix!

1055
01:22:34,199 --> 01:22:35,655
[barking]

1056
01:22:35,742 --> 01:22:40,202
And this is the payoff, you know,
because the Blind Man saved this dog,

1057
01:22:40,289 --> 01:22:42,951
now this dog is loyal to him
and saves him.

1058
01:22:43,542 --> 01:22:45,158
Karma, you would say.

1059
01:22:45,252 --> 01:22:47,414
-[dog growling]
-[grunting]

1060
01:22:55,888 --> 01:22:57,549
[barking]

1061
01:23:02,478 --> 01:23:04,185
[laughing] This is a lot of fun.

1062
01:23:07,357 --> 01:23:08,438
Now...

1063
01:23:09,610 --> 01:23:12,602
you're gonna see what I see.

1064
01:23:12,696 --> 01:23:14,812
Actually, that line
was not in the first movie.

1065
01:23:14,907 --> 01:23:16,693
It was just in the promotional material.

1066
01:23:16,783 --> 01:23:21,198
"Now you're going to see what I see.”
We decided to include it in this movie.

1067
01:23:21,288 --> 01:23:25,828
And [ think it plays great
for the eye-gouge thing.

1068
01:23:47,105 --> 01:23:52,771
The good news, she landed on top
of her mother and she was saved.

1069
01:23:52,861 --> 01:23:54,443
She didn't get hurt.

1070
01:24:00,202 --> 01:24:04,366
Now, this scene is the most important
scene in the whole movie.

1071
01:24:04,456 --> 01:24:08,745
This completes Norman's arc.

1072
01:24:10,420 --> 01:24:12,582
To this point, you don't know
what he's going to do

1073
01:24:12,673 --> 01:24:15,290
when he finally gets to Phoenix.

1074
01:24:15,384 --> 01:24:17,250
And this is a surprise.

1075
01:24:17,344 --> 01:24:23,511
He actually sets her free
by confessing his crimes

1076
01:24:23,600 --> 01:24:28,219
and his past sins
and telling her who he truly is.

1077
01:24:33,944 --> 01:24:37,938
Everything he said...

1078
01:24:40,867 --> 01:24:42,153
is true.

1079
01:24:48,834 --> 01:24:55,126
He confesses his things to himself
as well, which is the hardest thing to do.

1080
01:24:55,966 --> 01:24:58,253
I have killed.

1081
01:25:03,807 --> 01:25:04,968
I--

1082
01:25:06,101 --> 01:25:11,267
In the first movie, he made it very clear
that he was not doing anything wrong.

1083
01:25:11,356 --> 01:25:13,893
He was just amending things.

1084
01:25:13,984 --> 01:25:17,852
Like he would just come up
with excuses for his behavior.

1085
01:25:18,655 --> 01:25:20,771
He said, "I didn't do this,
I didn't do that,"

1086
01:25:20,866 --> 01:25:25,201
and now he's coming around,
coming to terms with his true nature,

1087
01:25:25,287 --> 01:25:28,405
and with the horrible things
that he's done.

1088
01:25:28,498 --> 01:25:29,863
And I think...

1089
01:25:31,126 --> 01:25:36,872
he's actually feeling, himself,
the pain that he's caused to others.

1090
01:25:36,965 --> 01:25:39,832
The misery that he has caused to others.

1091
01:25:39,926 --> 01:25:43,885
And he feels it. He understands it.

1092
01:25:43,972 --> 01:25:46,714
And only then, he truly repents.

1093
01:25:48,018 --> 01:25:49,258
-Go!
-[gasps]

1094
01:25:51,396 --> 01:25:52,727
And releases her.

1095
01:26:07,120 --> 01:26:11,956
"He has integrated his shadow,”
Carl Jung would say.

1096
01:26:13,377 --> 01:26:15,118
And he accepts his destiny.

1097
01:26:18,215 --> 01:26:19,546
He's embarrassed.

1098
01:26:19,633 --> 01:26:23,877
And I think Stephen Lang gave an amazing,
awesome performance here.

1099
01:26:23,970 --> 01:26:26,257
Very honest and very raw.

1100
01:26:29,184 --> 01:26:30,174
[thud]

1101
01:26:32,020 --> 01:26:35,934
And now, he understands he's going to die.
He's not even fighting.

1102
01:26:37,192 --> 01:26:40,901
He just accepts his fate
and his punishment.

1103
01:26:44,116 --> 01:26:45,527
[thud, grunting]

1104
01:27:12,561 --> 01:27:13,926
Tara?

1105
01:27:28,201 --> 01:27:30,192
[grunting]

1106
01:27:30,287 --> 01:27:33,655
I love this setup.
The lighting here is beautiful.

1107
01:27:33,749 --> 01:27:37,413
The sun is slowly coming out.

1108
01:27:38,211 --> 01:27:39,576
[Phoenix] No.

1109
01:27:39,671 --> 01:27:40,911
[grunts]

1110
01:27:41,590 --> 01:27:42,625
No.

1111
01:27:43,258 --> 01:27:44,339
No.

1112
01:27:49,139 --> 01:27:50,629
Please.

1113
01:27:50,724 --> 01:27:55,264
And the Blind Man makes it clear to her
that it's his time

1114
01:27:55,353 --> 01:27:57,390
and that he's okay with it.

1115
01:27:58,398 --> 01:27:59,888
Let me help you.

1116
01:28:01,693 --> 01:28:03,309
I can save you.

1117
01:28:07,741 --> 01:28:10,324
And he says that she already saved him

1118
01:28:10,410 --> 01:28:15,996
because she pushed him to confess
and come to terms with his true nature

1119
01:28:16,082 --> 01:28:21,452
and acknowledge the monster
that lives inside of him.

1120
01:28:29,971 --> 01:28:32,087
And to stop living in denial.

1121
01:28:44,486 --> 01:28:49,276
And we decided to keep this scene,
this beat without any music.

1122
01:28:49,366 --> 01:28:52,984
Because, you know, sometimes music--
It only kicks in here at the end,

1123
01:28:53,078 --> 01:28:56,321
but throughout the scene,
there's no music.

1124
01:28:56,414 --> 01:28:58,246
It tells you how you should feel
about a scene,

1125
01:28:58,333 --> 01:29:01,997
and we wanted this
to be very somber and raw.

1126
01:29:02,087 --> 01:29:04,545
You know, the man is dying.

1127
01:29:04,631 --> 01:29:08,625
He deserved to die at that point,

1128
01:29:08,718 --> 01:29:12,052
and we're not giving him a heroic death.

1129
01:29:12,138 --> 01:29:14,095
It's just-- It is what it is.

1130
01:29:14,182 --> 01:29:19,973
We're just witnessing how he slowly
fades away without glorifying anything.

1131
01:29:20,063 --> 01:29:22,930
And I think it works great.

1132
01:29:25,944 --> 01:29:30,359
I love this shot here.
This is a new beginning for her.

1133
01:29:31,199 --> 01:29:33,531
Her performance is beautiful, too.

1134
01:29:33,618 --> 01:29:36,861
And what Pedro did with the light
in those shots is also amazing.

1135
01:29:56,099 --> 01:29:57,089
[Phoenix] Hey.

1136
01:29:59,185 --> 01:30:00,596
Hey.

1137
01:30:01,646 --> 01:30:03,557
Think there's room for one more?

1138
01:30:05,108 --> 01:30:06,189
I'm sure there is.

1139
01:30:08,153 --> 01:30:09,268
What's your name?

1140
01:30:13,992 --> 01:30:15,858
My name is Phoenix.

1141
01:30:15,952 --> 01:30:17,442
And there we go.

1142
01:30:17,537 --> 01:30:19,653
[rock music playing]

1143
01:30:21,374 --> 01:30:27,620
These final credits here,
our editing team put this together.

1144
01:30:27,714 --> 01:30:30,376
They did an amazing job.
I think they look beautiful.

1145
01:30:30,467 --> 01:30:32,458
[electric guitar playing]

1146
01:30:43,104 --> 01:30:49,521
By the way, that guitar playing there
in the back, that's me.

1147
01:30:49,611 --> 01:30:52,023
Roque Banos asked me to record it.

1148
01:30:52,113 --> 01:30:54,901
So it was a privilege
to be able to play that.

1149
01:31:00,830 --> 01:31:03,071
I love this one, particularly.

1150
01:31:03,166 --> 01:31:04,702
[rock music continues]

1151
01:31:28,733 --> 01:31:31,395
So there it is.

1152
01:31:31,486 --> 01:31:35,605
Thank you guys so much.
I hope you enjoyed the movie.

1153
01:31:35,699 --> 01:31:38,316
Oh, we got this one coming. Yeah, sure.

1154
01:31:39,035 --> 01:31:41,402
The final coda.

1155
01:31:41,496 --> 01:31:44,909
Is he alive, huh? We don't know that.

1156
01:31:46,584 --> 01:31:47,289
Thank you, guys. Thank you, guys.

1157
01:31:47,293 --> 01:31:48,283
Thank you, guys. Thank you, guys.

1158
01:31:48,378 --> 01:31:51,541
I hope you enjoyed the movie
and you enjoyed this commentary.

1159
01:31:51,631 --> 01:31:54,214
And I hope to see you around soon.

1160
01:31:54,300 --> 01:31:55,335
Thank you.

